The term Mao-Spontex (German: Sponti, Sponti-Szene) refers to a political movement in the Marxist and libertarian movements in Western Europe from 1960 to 1970. The neologism is composed of "Maoist " and "spontaneist". The complete and accurate writing of this term would be Mao-spontaneity. The word "Spontex" can also be understood as a pejorative reference in reference to the sponge scraper brand Spontex.


